tachyon.worker.block

Class BlockDataManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • tachyon.worker.block.BlockDataManager

  • public class BlockDataManager
extends Object
    Class is responsible for managing the Tachyon BlockStore and Under FileSystem. This class is thread-safe.

      • addCheckpoint

        public void addCheckpoint(long userId,
                 int fileId)
                   throws org.apache.thrift.TException,
                          IOException
        Add the checkpoint information of a file. The information is from the user userId. This method is normally triggered from FileOutStream.close() if and only if WriteType.isThrough() is true. The current implementation of checkpointing is that through WriteType operations write to UnderFileSystem on the client's write path, but under a user temp directory (temp directory is defined in the worker as getUserUfsTmpFolder(long)).
        Parameters:
        userId - The user id of the client who sends the notification
        fileId - The id of the checkpointed file
        Throws:
        org.apache.thrift.TException - if the file does not exist or cannot be renamed
        IOException - if the update to the master fails

      • cleanupUsers

        public void cleanupUsers()
                  throws IOException
        Cleans up after users, to prevent zombie users. This method is called periodically.
        Throws:
        IOException

      • commitBlock

        public void commitBlock(long userId,
               long blockId)
                 throws IOException
        Commits a block to Tachyon managed space. The block must be temporary. The block is persisted after BlockStore.commitBlock(long, long). The block will not be accessible until MasterClient.worker_cacheBlock(long, long, long, long, long) succeeds
        Parameters:
        userId - The id of the client
        blockId - The id of the block to commit
        Throws:
        IOException - if the block to commit does not exist

      • createBlock

        public String createBlock(long userId,
                 long blockId,
                 int tierAlias,
                 long initialBytes)
                   throws IOException,
                          OutOfSpaceException
        Creates a block in Tachyon managed space. The block will be temporary until it is committed.
        Parameters:
        userId - The id of the client
        blockId - The id of the block to create
        tierAlias - The alias of the tier to place the new block in, -1 for any tier
        initialBytes - The initial amount of bytes to be allocated
        Returns:
        A string representing the path to the local file
        Throws:
        IOException - if the block already exists
        OutOfSpaceException - if there is no more space to store the block

      • createBlockRemote

        public void createBlockRemote(long userId,
                     long blockId,
                     int tierAlias,
                     long initialBytes)
                       throws FileDoesNotExistException,
                              IOException
        Creates a block. This method is only called from a data server. Call getTempBlockWriterRemote(long, long) to get a writer for writing to the block.
        Parameters:
        userId - The id of the client
        blockId - The id of the block to be created
        tierAlias - The alias of the tier to place the new block in, -1 for any tier
        initialBytes - The initial amount of bytes to be allocated
        Throws:
        FileDoesNotExistException - if the block is not on the worker
        IOException - if the block writer cannot be obtained
